1. GRANT OF LICENCE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Subject to the terms of a valid, signed PFF-TRUST Partner Agreement and the
payment of the applicable Sovereign Licence Fee, the Licensor grants to the
approved institution ("the Licensee") a:

  • NON-EXCLUSIVE — no other licensee's rights are diminished
  • NON-TRANSFERABLE — cannot be assigned, sublicensed, or resold
  • REVOCABLE — Licensor may terminate for breach with 14 days' notice
  • LIMITED — strictly for integration into the Licensee's CBN-licensed
    financial services platform

right to access and integrate the Software's public API surface within
the Licensee's production environment.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
2. RESTRICTIONS — WHAT YOU MAY NOT DO
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

The Licensee SHALL NOT, and shall ensure that its officers, employees,
contractors, and agents do not:

  a) Copy, reproduce, or distribute the Software or any portion thereof to
     any third party without the prior written consent of the Licensor.

  b) Reverse-engineer, decompile, disassemble, decrypt, or otherwise attempt
     to derive the source code, biometric algorithms, cryptographic keys, or
     BSSS protocol specification from any compiled artefact.

  c) Modify, adapt, translate, or create derivative works based upon the
     Software, in whole or in part.

  d) Sublicense, sell, rent, lease, transfer, assign, or otherwise
     commercially exploit the Software to any third party.

  e) Remove, obscure, or alter any proprietary notices, copyright marks,
     trademarks, or legends contained in or on the Software.

  f) Use the Software in any manner that violates:
       — Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) Agent Banking Guidelines
       — Nigeria Data Protection Act (NDPA) 2023
       — NITDA Information Security Policy
       — Financial Action Task Force (FATF) Recommendations
       — Any applicable Anti-Money Laundering (AML) / Know Your Customer
         (KYC) regulation enforceable in the Federal Republic of Nigeria.

  g) Store raw biometric data — fingerprints, facial geometry, iris scans —
     in any database, log file, network packet, or persistent medium.
     The BSSS (Biometric System Security Standard) mandates that only
     cryptographically signed SUCCESS_TOKENs leave the user's device.

  h) Hard-code Sovereign API Keys, BSSS_MASTER_SECRET values, DATABASE_URLs,
     BVN_PEPPER values, or any cryptographic secret into source code or
     commit them to any version-control system.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
3. SOVEREIGN API KEY & LICENCE FEE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  • Each Licensee is issued one (1) Sovereign API Key per approved hostAppId.
  • The annual Sovereign Licence Fee is ₦500,000 (Five Hundred Thousand Naira),
    payable in advance on the anniversary of the Partner Agreement date.
  • Keys are revoked automatically on the first day following non-renewal.
  • Emergency suspension (within 1 hour) is available to the Licensor at any
    time for breach of this Licence or CBN directive.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
